adGenAOSNetSyncMib.name: adGenAOSNetSyncMib

revisions.description: The following changes have been made in this version: 1. Add a trap for the T4 interface output squelch.
The following changes have been made in this version: 1. Removed the LTI State from the clock defects trap. 2. Added a new trap for the LTI State change.
Created the adGenAosNetSync MIB. Revision R10.11

adGenAOSNetSyncMib.contactinfo: Technical Support Dept. Postal: ADTRAN, Inc. 901 Explorer Blvd. Huntsville, AL 35806 Tel: +1 800 726-8663 Fax: +1 256 963 6217 E-mail: support@adtran.com
adGenAOSNetSyncMib.description: The MIB module defines Network Sync configuration information and traps for AdtranOS products.

adGenAOSNetSyncTrapEnable.name: adGenAOSNetSyncTrapEnable
adGenAOSNetSyncTrapEnable.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the Network Sync trap.

adGenAOSNetSyncLTIState.name: adGenAOSNetSyncLTIState
adGenAOSNetSyncLTIState.description: A numerical representation of the chassis's LTI(Loss of Timing Info) state.

adGenAOSNetSyncClockNumber.name: adGenAOSNetSyncClockNumber
adGenAOSNetSyncClockNumber.description: A numerical representation of the chassis's Network Sync Clock source.

adGenAOSNetSyncClockDefectStatus.name: adGenAOSNetSyncClockDefectStatus
adGenAOSNetSyncClockDefectStatus.description: This variable indicates the Network Sync clock defect status. The adGenAOSNetSyncClockDefectStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore, it can represent multiple defects simultaneously. Bit 1 which represents no defects must be set if and only if no other bits are set. The various bit positions are: 1 NONE No defects 2 LOS Loss of signal 4 EFD Exceeded frequency deviation 8 LO_ESMC Loss of ESMC 16 QL_FAILED Quality level failed

adGenAOSNetSyncT4SquelchState.name: adGenAOSNetSyncT4SquelchState
adGenAOSNetSyncT4SquelchState.description: A numerical representation of the T4 interface squelch state.

adGenAOSNetSyncClockDefectTrap.name: adGenAOSNetSyncClockDefectTrap
adGenAOSNetSyncClockDefectTrap.description: A Network Sync trap signifies a change in clock defect status.

adGenAOSNetSyncLTIStateChangeTrap.name: adGenAOSNetSyncLTIStateChangeTrap
adGenAOSNetSyncLTIStateChangeTrap.description: A Network Sync trap signifies a change in Loss of timing state.

adGenAOSNetSyncT4SquelchStateChangeTrap.name: adGenAOSNetSyncT4SquelchStateChangeTrap
adGenAOSNetSyncT4SquelchStateChangeTrap.description: A Network Sync trap signifies a change in T4 interface squelch state.

adGenAOSNetSyncFullCompliance.name: adGenAOSNetSyncFullCompliance
adGenAOSNetSyncFullCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement version 2 of the adGenAosNetSync MIB. When this MIB is implemented with support for read-write, then such an implementation can claim full compliance.

adGenAOSNetSyncTrapCfgGroup.name: adGenAOSNetSyncTrapCfgGroup
adGenAOSNetSyncTrapCfgGroup.description: This group contains the objects necessary to enable/disable NetSync failure traps.

adGenAOSNetSyncTrapGroup.name: adGenAOSNetSyncTrapGroup
adGenAOSNetSyncTrapGroup.description: The objects necessary to control NetSync notification messages.

adGenAOSNetSyncNotificationGroup.name: adGenAOSNetSyncNotificationGroup
adGenAOSNetSyncNotificationGroup.description: Traps which may be used to enhance event driven management of the chassis's Network Sync.
